Install brew from the instructions given in the link below.

https://brew.sh/
After installing Homebrew, create a file named ".curlrc" in the user's home directory. The content of the file should be "-k" followed by a newline character

Steps:

OpenTerminal
Execute below command
# echo -k > ~/.curlrc
# Execute below command to see -k in file ~/.curlrc
# cat ~/.curlrc
Run all the below commands in Terminal

(virtualbox command is not For MacOs M1/M2)
# brew install --cask virtualbox 
# brew install --cask vagrant
# brew install --cask vagrant-manager
# brew install git
# brew install openjdk@17
# sudo ln -sfn $HOMEBREW_PREFIX/opt/openjdk@17/libexec/openjdk.jdk /Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/openjdk.jdk
# exec zsh -l
# brew install maven
# brew install --cask visual-studio-code
# brew install --cask intellij-idea
